{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}'''Yang Earth Monkey'''{{жЛЉйЯ≥|w√єshƒУn}}гАБ{{ж≥®йЯ≥|гД®ЋЛ гДХгД£}}гАБ{{lang-ko|лђімЛ†}}гАБ{{lang-vi|{{Unicode|MбЇ≠u Th√Ґn}}}}) is one of the components of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|еЕ≠еНБеє≤жФѓ}}.

It is the 45th combination in the comprehensive sexagenary cycle, preceded by {{ill|Dingwei|ja|дЄБжЬ™}} and followed by {{ill|Jiyou|ja|еЈ±йЕЙ}}. In the {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements theory|ja|йЩ∞йЩљдЇФи°МжАЭжГ≥|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory}}, the heavenly stem {{ill|Wu|ja|жИК|1=Tsuchinoe (жИК)}} represents yang earth, and the earthly branch {{ill|Shen|ja|зФ≥}} represents yang metal; according to the principle of {{ill|phase generation|ja|зЫЄзФЯ}} (earth producing metal).

