=== Events ===
* In {{ill|Meiji|ja|жШОж≤ї|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 41 (1908) вАУ the issuance of the {{ill|Wushen Edict|ja|жИКзФ≥и©ФжЫЄ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* In 1968 вАУ the Tet Offensive during the {{ill|Vietnam War|ja|гГЩгГИгГКгГ†жИ¶дЇЙ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In Vietnamese, it is referred to as {{Unicode|Sбї± kiбїЗn TбЇњt MбЇ≠u Th√Ґn}} (Incident Festival Wushen).

== The Month of Wushen ==
In years whose last digit in the Western calendar is 2 or 7 (corresponding to the heavenly stems {{ill|Ren|ja|е£ђ|1=Mizunoe (е£ђ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Ding|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}), the month of July is designated as the month of Wushen. (Note that in this context, вАЬmonthвАЭ may refer to a lunar month or a seasonal period [from {{ill|Rissh≈Ђ|ja|зЂЛзІЛ|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to the day before {{ill|Hakuro|ja|зЩљйЬ≤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}].)

== The Day of Wushen ==
=== Date Selection ===
The day of Wushen is the 16th day (the final day) of the {{ill|Tengitenj≈Н|ja|е§©дЄАе§©дЄК|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

