In years whose last digit in the Western calendar is 2 or 7 (corresponding to the heavenly stems {{ill|Ren|ja|е£ђ|1=Mizunoe (е£ђ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and {{ill|Ding|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}), the month of July is designated as the month of Wushen. (Note that in this context, вАЬmonthвАЭ may refer to a lunar month or a seasonal period [from {{ill|Rissh≈Ђ|ja|зЂЛзІЛ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} to the day before {{ill|Hakuro|ja|зЩљйЬ≤|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}].)

