* In 1968 вАУ the Tet Offensive during the {{ill|Vietnam War|ja|гГЩгГИгГКгГ†жИ¶дЇЙ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Vietnam War|qq=}}. In Vietnamese, it is referred to as {{Unicode|Sбї± kiбїЗn TбЇњt MбЇ≠u Th√Ґn|qq=}} (Incident Festival Wushen).

== The Month of Wushen ==
In years whose last digit in the Western calendar is 2 or 7 (corresponding to the heavenly stems {{ill|Ren|ja|е£ђ|1=Mizunoe (е£ђ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ren|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizunoe (е£ђ)|qq=}} and {{ill|Ding|ja|дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|lt=Hinoto (дЄБ)|2=ja|3=дЄБ|4=zh|5=дЄБ|1=Hinoto (дЄБ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ding|13=User:Immanuelle/Hinoto (дЄБ)|qq=}}), the month of July is designated as the month of Wushen. (Note that in this context, вАЬmonthвАЭ may refer to a lunar month or a seasonal period [from {{ill|Rissh≈Ђ|ja|зЂЛзІЛ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rissh≈Ђ|qq=}} to the day before {{ill|Hakuro|ja|зЩљйЬ≤|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakuro|qq=}}].)

== The Day of Wushen ==
=== Date Selection ===
The day of Wushen is the 16th day (the final day) of the {{ill|Tengitenj≈Н|ja|е§©дЄАе§©дЄК|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tengitenj≈Н|qq=}}.

